s, which may include your\nemail address when you use your email address as your user name.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h3><b>Tracking,\nAnonymous Tracking, Do Not Track<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>Depending on your\nuser preferences, we may track your activities on Simplicity Studio by your\nuser ID or anonymously.  If we collect your data anonymously, your data will be\ncombined with data from all other users and will not be associated with you or\nyour user ID in any manner. If you set your user preferences to allow us to\ntrack you anonymously, your use and access to Simplicity Studio will be\nrestricted to &ldquo;unrestricted&rdquo; areas and files within Simplicity Studio.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you set your user\npreferences to &ldquo;Do not track&rdquo; we will not collect any data concerning your use\nof Simplicity Studio and your use and access to Simplicity Studio will be\nrestricted to &ldquo;unrestricted&rdquo; areas and files within Simplicity Studio.<\/p>\n\n<p>You may change your\nuser preferences concerning tracking at any time.  If you change your tracking\npreference to &ldquo;Anonymous&rdquo; we will remove your user ID from all information that\nwe collect from that time forward.  If you change your user preference to &ldquo;Do\nnot track&rdquo; we will not collect any data concerning your future use of\nSimplicity Studio.<\/p>\n\n<p>The information we\ncollect automatically is statistical data and may include personal information\nsuch as your user ID, or we may maintain it or associate it with personal\ninformation we collect in other ways or receive from third parties. It helps us\nto improve Simplicity Studio and to deliver a better and more personalized\nservice, including by enabling us to:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Estimate\nour audience size and usage patterns.<\/li>\n\n<li>Store\ninformation about your preferences, allowing us to customize Simplicity Studio\naccording to your individual interests.<\/li>\n\n<li>Remember\nyour user preferences.<\/li>\n\n<li>Recognize\nyou when you return to Simplicity Studio.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h3><b>How We\nUse Your Information<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>We use information\nthat we collect about you or that you provide to us, including any personal information\nto:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Provide\nyou with information, products, or services that you request from us.<\/li>\n\n<li>Fulfill\nany other purpose for which you provide it.<\/li>\n\n<li>Notify\nyou about changes to Simplicity Studio or any products or services we offer or\nprovide though it.<\/li>\n\n<li>Help\nus define future hardware products.<\/li>\n\n<li>Help\nus improve software features associated with Simplicity Studio.<\/li>\n\n<li>Make\nour content more relevant to our users.<\/li>\n\n<li>Determine\nour geographical customer base.<\/li>\n\n<li>Improve\nthe overall quality of Simplicity Studio. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h3><b>Disclosure of Your Information<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>We may disclose\naggregated information about our users, and information that does not identify\nany individual, without restriction. <\/p>\n\n<p>We may disclose\npersonal information that we collect or you provide as described in this Privacy\nStatement:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>To\nour subsidiaries and affiliates.<\/li>\n\n<li>To\ncontractors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our\nbusiness and who are bound by contractual obligations to keep personal\ninformation confidential and use it only for the purposes for which we disclose\nit to them.<\/li>\n\n<li>To\na buyer or other successor in the event of a merger, divestiture,\nrestructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some\nor all of Silicon Labs&rsquo; assets, whether as a going concern or as part of\nbankruptcy, liquidation, or similar proceeding, in which personal information\nheld by Silicon Labs about Simplicity Studio users is among the assets\ntransferred.<\/li>\n\n<li>To\nfulfill the purpose for which you provide it. For example, if you give us an\nemail address to use the &quot;email a friend&quot; feature of Simplicity\nStudio, we will transmit the contents of that email and your email address to\nthe recipients.<\/li>\n\n<li>For\nany other purpose disclosed by us when you provide the information.<\/li>\n\n<li>With\nyour consent.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>We may also disclose\nyour personal information:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>To\ncomply with any court order, law, or legal process, including to respond to any\ngovernment or regulatory request.<\/li>\n\n<li>To\nenforce or apply these Terms of Use.<\/li>\n\n<li>If\nwe believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect our rights, property,\nor safety or that of our customers or other third parties. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h3><b>Choices\nAbout How We Collect Your Information<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>We strive to provide\nyou with choices regarding the personal information you provide to us. We have\ncreated mechanisms to provide you with the following control over your\ninformation: <\/p>\n\n<p>You can set your user preferences to\ncontrol whether and how we collect information concerning your use of\nSimplicity Studio.  You can set your User Experience as follows:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Simplicity Studio login experience tracking<\/b> \u2013 We will collect information about your\nuser experience and it will be associated with your user ID.  You will have\naccess to all areas of Simplicity Studio.<\/li>\n\n<li>\n<b>Anonymous experience tracking<\/b>\n\u2013 We will collect information about your user experience and it will NOT be\nassociated with your user ID.  Your information will be combined with all\nothers users&rsquo; data.  You will have access only to unrestricted areas of\nSimplicity Studio.<\/li>\n\n<li>\n<b>Do not track experience<\/b>\n\u2013 We will not collect any information about your user experience.  You will\nhave access only to unrestricted areas of Simplicity Studio. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>You can review and\nchange your personal information by logging into your account on the CRM. You\nmay access the Salesforce.com CRM at www.siliconlabs.force.com. <\/p>\n\n<p>You can change your\nUser Experience settings at any time. <\/p>\n\n<h3><b>Data\nSecurity<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>We have implemented\nmeasures designed to secure your personal information from accidental loss and\nfrom unauthorized access, use, alteration, and disclosure. All information you\nprovide to us is stored on our secure servers behind firewalls. <\/p>\n\n<p>The safety and\nsecurity of your information also depends on you. Where we have given you (or\nwhere you have chosen) a password for access to certain parts of Simplicity\nStudio, you are responsible for keeping this password confidential. We ask you\nnot to share your password with anyone.<\/p>\n\n<p>Unfortunately, the\ntransmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although\nwe do our best to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security\nof your personal information transmitted to Simplicity Studio. Any transmission\nof personal information is at your own risk. We are not responsible for\ncircumvention of any privacy settings or security measures contained on\nSimplicity Studio. <\/p>\n\n<h3><b>Changes\nto Our Privacy Statement<\/b><\/h3>\n\n<p>It is our policy to\npost any changes we make to our Privacy Statement with a notice that the Terms\nof Use and Privacy Statement has been updated on Simplicity Studio home page.\nThe date the Terms of Use and Privacy Statement was last revised is identified\nat the top of the page.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n\n<\/body>\n\n<\/html>\n","id":1,"title":"Simplicity Studio Terms of Use and Privacy Statement"},{"softwareCovered":["Eclipse RCP 4.23.0.v20220308-0722"],"text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"ISO-8859-1\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1\" />\n<title>Eclips